1. Shipping experience - Evaluates efficiency and timeliness of delivery.  
2. Product durability - Assesses how well the product withstands wear.  
3. Comfort level - Measures the ease and comfort of use.  
4. Assembly ease - Indicates how simple or complex assembly is.  
5. Value for money - Assesses the product's worth relative to its price.  
6. Customer service - Evaluates the responsiveness and helpfulness of support.  
7. Product material - Describes the quality and type of materials used.  
8. Design appeal - Evaluates the aesthetic attractiveness of the product.  
9. Brand reputation - Considers the manufacturer's credibility and trustworthiness.  
10. User recommendations - Reflects suggestions or advice from previous buyers.  
